8. I try to keep in-character most of the time but if I worry too much about it it'll fill me with self-doubt..... I don't need more of that when I write! So at a certain point I won't worry too much about canon personality and allow myself to make a few adjustments

7. Heck yeah rarepairs!! The lack of content is frustrating, but if the chemistry is there, there you go!
Generally, any fic or art of a rarepair will have me rooting for them.
6. I've only ever made one-shots lol...... I think I'm too intimidated to seriously try multi-chapter writing~~ Maybe that'll change someday!!

5. My fics are DEFINITELY on the shorter end. Probably averages 1,500 words I'd say. I need to start focusing and expanding on a singular project-- I know I can get more mileage out of some of the ideas I've written

Past tense is always dependable, but present tense, while harder to do, can affect me deeply if it's done right. I've yet to try present tense, and I'm afraid I'll switch in-and-out of tenses if I do........

3. I only wrote fanfic in 1st-person once, and that was in the form of a letter. Otherwise, 3rd-person is the perspective I go for. I do like when fics can pull off 1st-person though, it creates a unique narration and sometimes more drama!

2. Sometimes I ask my brother to beta, but usually I just go it alone. It's not that I don't appreciate feedback, it's just that I'm afraid I'll have bias towards my own direction and writing and end up disregarding what the other person is saying. I don't want to be like that!!!
